text: Notable that Iowans are demanding detailed climate action plans in a lot of these candidate forums. They are really boring down and wanting details. Not content with vague calls to action.

text: Times change. Iowan tells @CoryBooker school privatization=segregation. "Your question is right spot on." Then stemwinder against Betsy DeVos (a one-time ally) and school privatization (a cause he once championed).

text: Though it may not seem so from cable news, Beto is not the only one packing rooms in rural Iowa. Awaiting @CoryBooker in Ottumwa.

text: A lot of focus on voter suppression by @BetoORourke Slams Texas voter rules that allow you to use concealed weapon permit to access voting booth, but not university id. “It shows you who is supposed to and who is not supposed to vote in Texas”
author: evanhalper

text: He also confessed rocking out to Joan Jett. Any Gen Xer should be able to relate.
author: evanhalper

text: One book @BetoORourke is reading right now: Unhabitable Earth. Climate change was a focal point of his remarks at every stop since he launched yesterday.
author: evanhalper

text: “I have enjoyed white privilege absolutely, undeniably” @BetoORourke says. His example: two serious arrests and didn’t ruin his life the way it may have others.
author: evanhalper

text: “The criticism is right on” @BetoORourke said of “ham handed” way he has talked about leaving his wife home with the kids as he has been off exploring and campaigning. “It’s made me a better candidate”
author: evanhalper

text: In an echo of Texas run, @BetoORourke makes a pledge ”You will not hear me demean or villify another candidate.”
author: evanhalper

text: New. He’s dazzled the media with his mini van driving skills. He’s lit up Twitter jumping on coffee counters. But @BetoORourke has a lot of work to do to win over caucus voters. On the ground in Iowa.
